      "block_id": "p9_b29",
      "translation": "Notes:"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p9_b30",
      "translation": "(7) The new business value of each segment includes retirement business, presented on a local statutory basis, excluding unallocated Group head office expenses and before deduction of non-controlling interests."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p9_b31",
      "translation": "(1) From 2017 onwards, financial information is reported on a financial year ended 31 December basis. Financial information for 2016 is reported on a financial year ended 30 November basis."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p9_b32",
      "translation": "(8) From 2019 onwards, annualized new premiums and new business value of other markets include our share of results from our 49% stake in Tata AIA Life Insurance Company Limited (Tata AIA Life). Annualized new premiums and new business value reported for 2018 and prior years have not been restated and do not include any contribution from Tata AIA Life. From 2019 onwards, the Group's new business value excludes new business value attributable to non-controlling interests. New business value for 2018 and prior years has not been restated and, as previously disclosed, was not adjusted for non-controlling interests. Tata AIA Life's IFRS results are accounted for using the equity method. The Group's consolidated financial statements use Tata AIA Life's financial information on a one-quarter lag basis. For clarity, total weighted premium income does not include any contribution from Tata AIA Life."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p9_b33",
      "translation": "(2) New business value is the present value of the estimated after-tax statutory profit expected to be generated by new business sold during the period, calculated at the time of sale, less the cost of capital required to support the new business in excess of statutory reserves."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p9_b34",
      "translation": "(3) Annualized new premiums is a measure of the level of new business, calculated as the sum of 100% of annualized first year premiums and 10% of single premiums, before reinsurance ceded."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p9_b35",
      "translation": "(4) Operating profit after tax presented is after deduction of non-controlling interests."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p9_b36",
      "translation": "(5) Total weighted premium income comprises 100% of renewal premiums, 100% of first year premiums and 10% of single premiums, before reinsurance ceded."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p9_b37",
      "translation": "(9) AIA has changed its IFRS accounting treatment for the recognition and measurement of insurance contract liabilities for Hong Kong participating business to reflect expected changes in policyholder dividends. Comparative information for 2019 has been adjusted. Comparative information for 2018 and prior years has not been restated."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p9_b38",
      "translation": "(6) Embedded value is the estimated economic value of life insurance business determined using actuarial methods based on a series of specific assumptions about future experience, but excludes the economic value of any future new business. Embedded value equity is the sum of embedded value, goodwill and other intangible assets."
    }
  ]
}
